A replicate-based data of 10 genotypes cultivated in 14 environments

data_ge.Rd

This dataset contain data on two variables assessed in 10 genotypes growing in in 11 environments. The experimental design was a RCBD with 3 replicates(blocks). This data provide examples for several functions of METAAB package.

Arguments

ENV

A factor with 14 levels; each level represents one cultivation environment.
GEN

A factor with 10 levels; each level represents one genotype.
REP

A factor with 3 levels; each level represents one replication/block.
GY

A continuous variable (grain yield) observed in each plot.
HM

A continuous variable (hectoliter mass) observed in each plot.
